00:52:28.090 --> 00:52:31.620
Then we can treat 1/N
as a small parameter

00:52:31.620 --> 00:52:34.540
and then do one
of the expansions.

00:52:34.540 --> 00:52:36.760
OK.

00:52:36.760 --> 00:52:38.540
So that's the rough idea.

00:52:38.540 --> 00:52:41.150
And then you get a
small parameter of 1/N.

00:52:41.150 --> 00:52:43.270
So in real life,
